---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-comparison', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'network-and-claims', text: 'Network and Claims', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-should-choose', text: 'Who Should Choose Which', level: 2 },
  { id: 'verdict', text: 'Our Verdict', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'BUPA Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'IMG Global Review', href: '/providers/img-global' },
  { title: 'Best Budget Insurance', href: '/best/budget-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Thailand Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/thailand/insurance' },
  { title: 'UK Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/uk/insurance' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'BUPA Global' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { feature: 'Inpatient Care', bupa: true, img: true },
  { feature: 'Outpatient Care', bupa: true, img: true },
  { feature: 'Annual Maximum', bupa: 'Unlimited', img: '$1M - $8M' },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', bupa: 'Full parity', img: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Maternity', bupa: 'Up to $75,000', img: 'Limited ($5-10K)' },
  { feature: 'Dental', bupa: 'Included (Premier+)', img: 'Add-on' },
  { feature: 'Vision', bupa: 'Included (Premier+)', img: 'Add-on' },
  { feature: 'Medical Evacuation', bupa: true, img: '$500,000' },
  { feature: 'Pre-existing Conditions', bupa: 'Often covered', img: 'Usually excluded' },
  { feature: 'No-Claims Discount', bupa: true, img: false },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'BUPA Global' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 30', bupa: '$200-300/mo', img: '$75-120/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 45', bupa: '$350-450/mo', img: '$120-180/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 35', bupa: '$400-550/mo', img: '$150-220/mo' },
  { profile: 'Family of 4', bupa: '$700-950/mo', img: '$280-400/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="BUPA Global vs IMG Global"
  description="Compare BUPA Global and IMG Global international health insurance. Premium coverage versus budget-friendly options — see which fits your needs."
  headline="BUPA Global vs IMG Global: Premium vs Budget Coverage"
  subheadline="The most comprehensive option versus the most affordable. Here's how these opposite ends of the spectrum compare."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes from Both"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
    <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Bupa Global and IMG Global are both popular choices for international health insurance, but they serve different needs. Understanding their key differences will help you choose the right coverage for your situation abroad.
  </p>
  <p>
    Bupa Global is a UK-based insurer with a strong reputation in international health coverage. Their main comprehensive coverage and a solid reputation for claims handling. They're particularly popular among expats who want reliable coverage from an established brand, with mid-to-premium range with good value for the coverage provided.
  </p>
  <p>
    IMG Global is offering affordable international health insurance with flexible options. They're known for their budget-friendly plans that still provide solid coverage. They tend to attract budget-conscious expats and digital nomads, offering lower premiums with higher deductible options available.
  </p>
  <p>
    This comparison breaks down the key differences between these two providers so you can make an informed decision. We'll cover coverage options, pricing estimates, network access, claims processes, and help you determine which one makes more sense for your specific needs and budget.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">BUPA Global</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li><strong>Trustpilot:</strong> 4.4/5 stars</li>
        <li>Mental health parity (equal to physical)</li>
        <li>Pre-existing conditions often covered</li>
        <li>Dental/vision included in top tiers</li>
        <li>No-claims discount available</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">IMG Global</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li><strong>Trustpilot:</strong> 4.6/5 stars</li>
        <li>Lowest premiums in category</li>
        <li>Deductibles up to $25,000 available</li>
        <li>50% deductible waived outside US</li>
        <li>High coverage limits ($8M)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    The price difference is dramatic — IMG Global can cost 50-70% less than BUPA Global. The question is what you're giving up for those savings.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Both Providers"
    description="Get quotes from BUPA Global and IMG Global for your situation."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="coverage-comparison">Coverage Comparison</h2>
  <p>
    This comparison highlights the premium vs budget trade-off clearly. BUPA Global includes benefits that IMG Global either limits or charges extra for.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Key Differences</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> BUPA Global treats mental health equally to physical health. IMG Global's coverage is more limited — a significant gap if mental health care matters to you.</li>
    <li><strong>Pre-existing conditions:</strong> BUPA Global often covers pre-existing conditions from the start. IMG Global typically excludes them.</li>
    <li><strong>Maternity:</strong> BUPA Global offers up to $75,000 for maternity. IMG Global's coverage is limited to $5-10,000.</li>
    <li><strong>Dental/vision:</strong> Included in BUPA's Premier and Elite plans. Add-on with IMG Global.</li>
    <li><strong>No-claims discount:</strong> BUPA rewards claim-free years. IMG does not.</li>
    <li><strong>Coverage limits:</strong> BUPA offers unlimited coverage. IMG caps at $8M (still very high).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    The price difference is substantial. BUPA Global typically costs 2-3x more than IMG Global for comparable age profiles.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <em>Prices based on comprehensive plans excluding US coverage. IMG Global prices can be significantly lower with higher deductibles.</em>
  </p>

  <h3>The Math</h3>
  <p>
    For a 35-year-old single expat, the annual difference is roughly:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>BUPA Global: ~$3,000/year</li>
    <li>IMG Global: ~$1,200/year</li>
    <li>Savings with IMG: ~$1,800/year</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Over 5 years, that's $9,000 in premium savings. The question is whether BUPA's additional benefits are worth that difference for your situation.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your Actual Price"
    description="See the real difference for your age, location, and needs."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="network-and-claims">Network and Claims</h2>

  <h3>Provider Networks</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>BUPA Global</strong> offers access to 1.7 million providers globally with good direct-billing availability in major hospitals.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>IMG Global</strong> has a smaller direct-billing network. You may need to pay upfront and claim reimbursement more often, though you can see any licensed provider.
  </p>

  <h3>Claims Process</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>BUPA Global</strong> has a strong claims reputation with fast settlements and few rejections. Their MembersWorld app handles digital claims.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>IMG Global</strong> actually edges BUPA on Trustpilot (4.6 vs 4.4), with customers praising reliable claim payments despite the lower premiums.
  </p>

  <h3>Customer Service</h3>
  <p>
    Both offer 24/7 multilingual support. BUPA Global includes access to in-house medical professionals. IMG Global is known for responsive service.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-should-choose">Who Should Choose Which</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose BUPA Global If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Mental health coverage is essential</li>
        <li>You have pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>You need strong maternity benefits</li>
        <li>You want dental/vision included</li>
        <li>All-inclusive coverage gives you peace of mind</li>
        <li>Budget is flexible for premium protection</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose IMG Global If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Minimizing premium cost is priority #1</li>
        <li>You're young and healthy</li>
        <li>You don't have pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>You don't need maternity coverage</li>
        <li>Mental health coverage isn't critical</li>
        <li>You can handle a high deductible</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    This isn't a close comparison — it's a choice between two fundamentally different products.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Choose BUPA Global</strong> if you want true comprehensive coverage with no gaps. Their mental health parity, pre-existing condition handling, and all-inclusive benefits justify the premium for people who need these features.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Choose IMG Global</strong> if you're healthy, young, and primarily want protection against catastrophic medical costs. Their 4.6/5 Trustpilot rating proves you can trust them to pay claims despite the low prices.
  </p>
  <p>
    For most healthy expats under 40 without complex health needs, IMG Global offers excellent value. For anyone with pre-existing conditions, mental health concerns, or family planning needs, BUPA Global is worth the investment.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Consider Your Actual Needs</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      Don't pay for benefits you won't use, but don't skimp on coverage you need. If you have any history of mental health treatment, pre-existing conditions, or might have children, BUPA's higher premiums could save you money in the long run.
    </p>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Decide?"
    description="Compare quotes from both providers based on your specific situation."
    buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices, coverage, and plan details change frequently. We are not insurance brokers. Verify all information with the providers before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
